         <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1862</unitdate>
         <abstract id="aspace_b512768094af75b2d97da476e3949def">The papers consist of correspondence and documents related to Frederick Townsend Ward's role as commanding officer of the "Ever Victorious Army" which helped crush the Taiping Rebellion in China (1850-1864). Material of a personal nature is minimal and pertains to his wedding arrangements.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_72ffd4feb3d460b06dc3784771db1b41">
            <language>The material is in Chinese. Brief English summaries are included.</language>
         </langmaterial>
